comments_data.body:
on one place it says `terminated by SIGABRT`, but later `crashed by signal: 11, si_code: 1` and also `crashed by signal: 4, si_code: 1`.

@Adel-Magebinary did this version of redis (any other versions of redis), ever worked for you on SmartOs?
can you find out which are signal 11 and 4? are these SIGSEGV and SIGILL?

@madolson  the system is running alpine image from your latest repo on dockerhub.
@oranagra  The kill signal changed after I changed the Redis configuration oom-score-adj to yes.

Yes the older version worked for me. I think it was 4.x worked fine with stop-writes-on-bgsave-error no.

The Redis was pumped constantly by Magento 2.4.2 cache.

@oranagra  yea, the issue might come from this line
```
entry = zmalloc(sizeof(*entry));
```

That the redis is trying to allocate the memory for the entry but libpthread.so somehow kills it.

@Adel-Magebinary maybe you can try downgrading back to the redis version that used to work (use it together with the new Magento).
Or try running redis with valgrind in some way.

i tried disassembling the code dump from the crash log, i think the crash is around the hashing of the member name, but so far it doesn't help conclude what's the problem.
